parallel
Class BoundedBufferArrayUnsynchronized

java.lang.Object
  parallel.BoundedBufferArrayUnsynchronized
public class BoundedBufferArrayUnsynchronized
extends java.lang.Object

a bounded-length FIFO buffer implemented as an Object Array that is totally unsynchronized. It's exactly the same as the BoundedBufferArray class, only that's completely unsynchronized (and the exceptions thrown are now IllegalStateException or IndexOutOfBoundsException.)

Title: popt4jlib

Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

remove

public int remove(java.lang.Object p,
                  int hintPos)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
removes the first argument from this buffer, starting the search from the index provided by the 2nd argument (which can possibly be greater than the current size of the buffer, in which case the search goes from the end of the buffer backwards).

Parameters:
p - Object the object reference to be removed must exist in the buffer for the search employs the reference equality test (==)
hintPos - int a hint on the index position to start the search
Returns:
int the position where the object was found
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the object is not found or if hintPos < 0 or if p is null
